The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for remote sensing data analysis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the challenges of handling large-scale data, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning for climate change and urbanization, which could fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning for information retrieval, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
